WEBVTT

00:00.834 --> 00:03.471
The sex was amazing. Shh...
With Lemon?!

00:03.504 --> 00:04.805
She's driving me crazy!
He's driving me crazy!

00:04.838 --> 00:07.275
I so told you that working
together was a bad idea.

00:07.308 --> 00:10.278
I booked you on the
Belles and Bachelors Cruise.

00:10.311 --> 00:11.812
I am not going on that cruise.

00:11.845 --> 00:13.781
And I am not saying it again.

00:13.814 --> 00:14.815
What do you mean that you booked

00:14.848 --> 00:16.184
Crickett and Stanley
in Fancie's?

00:16.216 --> 00:17.285
That's what you needed.

00:17.318 --> 00:18.352
Had I not convinced
Brando Wilkes

00:18.386 --> 00:19.353
to have his wedding.

00:19.387 --> 00:20.554
There's... one...

00:20.588 --> 00:22.156
teeny-tiny other thing.

00:22.190 --> 00:23.091
I'm getting married!

00:23.124 --> 00:24.058
(sighs)

00:24.092 --> 00:25.293
AnnaBeth Nass,
will you make me

00:25.326 --> 00:27.161
the happiest man in the world
and marry me?

00:27.195 --> 00:27.995
I didn't realize you all
were so serious.

00:28.028 --> 00:29.130
We are.
WADE: I'm not gonna be

00:29.163 --> 00:31.199
at the wedding 'cause
I'm gonna be down in Atlanta.

00:31.232 --> 00:33.367
It's where the next
Rammer Jammer's gonna be.

00:33.401 --> 00:35.403
You're moving?

00:35.436 --> 00:36.470
I am so happy for you.

00:41.142 --> 00:42.076
BlueBell...

00:42.110 --> 00:46.314
it is a beautiful day
for the apocalypse.

00:46.347 --> 00:48.282
Wade Kinsella's
moving to Atlanta

00:48.316 --> 00:49.850
to franchise the Rammer Jammer.

00:49.883 --> 00:54.422
Our Meatball is marrying that
lunatic Lily Anne Lonergan.

00:54.455 --> 00:57.091
Fancie's has burned and flooded.

00:57.125 --> 01:01.295
Mm, a biblical omen
if ever there was one.

01:01.329 --> 01:03.197
And AnnaBeth Nass
has been proposed to

01:03.231 --> 01:04.864
by that Gainey fella.

01:04.897 --> 01:07.368
And if she says yes,

01:07.401 --> 01:10.838
then BlueBell will be forever
connected to that vile Fillmore.

01:10.871 --> 01:12.440
Dash, we're sitting
right here.

01:12.473 --> 01:13.874
Mm.

01:13.907 --> 01:16.577
Prepare yourselves,
BlueBellians.

01:16.610 --> 01:17.845
The Four Horsemen

01:17.878 --> 01:20.448
will be galloping up
Main Street any minute.

01:20.481 --> 01:22.583
Well, someone needs to save us.

01:22.616 --> 01:23.584
But who?

01:23.617 --> 01:25.453
I mean, "whom."

01:25.486 --> 01:28.222
My grammar has left me.
Another omen.

01:28.256 --> 01:31.225
GEORGE: The insurance company
 isn't giving us a dime.

01:31.259 --> 01:32.360
I get that you think
that this is my fault.

01:32.393 --> 01:34.162
As does the
insurance investigator.

01:34.195 --> 01:37.331
(sighs)
George, I am so sorry that I...

01:37.365 --> 01:38.466
let you down.

01:38.499 --> 01:40.668
This partnership
means a lot to me.

01:40.701 --> 01:42.470
And so do you.

01:42.503 --> 01:45.473
You have an interesting way
of showing it.

01:45.506 --> 01:48.409
I know that I treated you badly,
and honestly...

01:48.442 --> 01:51.645
I don't know why
you drive me so crazy.

01:51.679 --> 01:55.183
And calling you a bad
business partner-- it was...

01:55.216 --> 01:58.152
it was out of line.

01:58.186 --> 02:01.689
Especially since I'm the one
who set our business on fire.

02:01.722 --> 02:03.324
But...

02:05.526 --> 02:06.594
(sighs)

02:08.628 --> 02:10.931
I'm gonna make this right.

02:10.964 --> 02:14.302
I'm gonna get you every cent
of your money back.

02:15.336 --> 02:16.704
I promise.

02:28.416 --> 02:30.251
Uh, you know, uh, no.
(laughs)

02:30.284 --> 02:32.586
This, uh... this "us"...

02:32.620 --> 02:33.954
This was a bad idea.

02:33.987 --> 02:34.955
No! That's not true.

02:34.988 --> 02:36.257
We actually make a great team.

02:36.290 --> 02:37.391
We just needed...

02:37.425 --> 02:39.527
And when... if...
(nervously chuckles)

02:39.560 --> 02:40.928
our now very...

02:40.961 --> 02:43.464
waterlogged business
ever dries out...

02:43.497 --> 02:44.665
you know what?

02:44.698 --> 02:45.666
It's all yours.

02:45.699 --> 02:47.235
Because...

02:47.268 --> 02:49.169
I'm done.

02:52.306 --> 02:54.174
Okay.

02:56.009 --> 02:57.445
I understand.
(laughs)

02:58.479 --> 03:01.349
Good, good.

03:01.382 --> 03:03.251
Now, if you'll excuse me,

03:03.284 --> 03:05.453
there are some others that
I have to make amends with.

03:08.989 --> 03:09.990
(water running)

03:10.023 --> 03:11.992
LAVON:
What's with you?

03:12.025 --> 03:14.695
Nothing. What's wrong with you?

03:14.728 --> 03:17.365
Nothing.

03:17.398 --> 03:19.967
You're upset about
A.B.'s proposal.

03:20.000 --> 03:21.769
No. No.
I'm glad she found someone

03:21.802 --> 03:23.437
who can give her what she wants.

03:24.738 --> 03:26.374
You're upset because
Wade is leaving.

03:26.407 --> 03:29.277
No. I am happy for Wade.
This is

03:29.310 --> 03:30.744
a great opportunity for him.
So what are you doing

03:30.778 --> 03:32.380
moping all over the place for?

03:32.413 --> 03:34.315
I'm just trying to think
of a good gift for him.

03:34.348 --> 03:35.483
You know? Something that says...

03:35.516 --> 03:37.451
"Good luck on your new
business endeavor,

03:37.485 --> 03:39.287
"about which I have
no particular feelings.

03:39.320 --> 03:40.554
"Save for a vague,

03:40.588 --> 03:42.022
neighborly pride."

03:42.055 --> 03:44.224
So, luggage tags?
(sighs)

03:47.361 --> 03:48.161
Nice.
Yeah.

03:51.532 --> 03:54.335
People, we have
three weddings to save.

03:54.368 --> 03:55.469
Sylvie and Brando have

03:55.503 --> 03:58.339
out of town guests
arriving any minute.

03:58.372 --> 04:00.541
Crickett and Stanley
are celebrating ten...

04:02.343 --> 04:03.444
fascinating years together.

04:03.477 --> 04:05.646
And Meatball and Lily Anne
are in some sort of rush.

04:07.648 --> 04:08.749
Their choice.

04:08.782 --> 04:10.618
And despite

04:10.651 --> 04:13.020
Fancie's sogginess...
we need to show them

04:13.053 --> 04:15.356
our BlueBellian spirit
and put these weddings on.

04:15.389 --> 04:17.391
Well, it's not our fault
you set Fancie's on fire.

04:18.459 --> 04:20.494
Sylvie and Brando
don't even live in BlueBell.

04:20.528 --> 04:22.296
Neither does
that crazy girl singer.

04:23.364 --> 04:24.398
I move that
the town does nothing.

04:24.432 --> 04:25.399
I second.

04:25.433 --> 04:27.067
These people
want to get married,

04:27.100 --> 04:28.769
that's their problem.

04:28.802 --> 04:30.404
What?!

04:30.438 --> 04:33.374
No! No! No! No!

04:33.407 --> 04:35.042
Now, come on now,
this is BlueBell.

04:35.075 --> 04:36.777
And-and like our
great founder,

04:36.810 --> 04:39.313
Cyrus Lavinius Jeremiah Jones...

04:39.347 --> 04:41.649
and all three of his wives,

04:41.682 --> 04:43.050
we-we love love.
(laughs)

04:43.083 --> 04:44.418
So, let-let's pitch in

04:44.452 --> 04:45.753
and-and make this weekend

04:45.786 --> 04:47.521
the most romantic weekend ever.

04:47.555 --> 04:49.089
Huh?

04:49.122 --> 04:51.291
(clears throat)

04:52.560 --> 04:53.661
(loudly clears throat)

04:54.762 --> 04:57.365
Hear! Hear!

04:57.398 --> 04:58.899
(applause)

05:00.568 --> 05:02.403
Yeah. Oh. Uh, um...

05:02.436 --> 05:03.837
I also have an announcement.

05:03.871 --> 05:05.839
Wanda has finally agreed
to the alpacas.

05:05.873 --> 05:07.107
They arrive today.

05:07.140 --> 05:09.076
(whoops, laughs)

05:09.109 --> 05:11.579
Uh... also, uh,
Wanda is pregnant. (laughs)

05:11.612 --> 05:13.681
(applause, cheering)

05:18.852 --> 05:21.389
Hey, AnnaBeth.

05:21.422 --> 05:22.823
Hi.

05:22.856 --> 05:23.857
So, uh...

05:23.891 --> 05:26.494
I heard about Davis' proposal.

05:26.527 --> 05:27.695
Congratulations.

05:27.728 --> 05:29.497
Yeah!
(laughs nervously)

05:29.530 --> 05:31.699
Actually, I told him
I need time to think.

05:31.732 --> 05:33.467
Right.
Mm-hmm.

05:33.501 --> 05:34.502
Well, uh...

05:34.535 --> 05:35.836
you know,
whatever you decide,

05:35.869 --> 05:36.870
good-good luck.

05:38.839 --> 05:40.574
I just hope you're happy.

05:40.608 --> 05:42.576
Okay. Well...
(sighs)

05:42.610 --> 05:44.344
you know, thanks for the hopes.

05:48.549 --> 05:50.851
(sighs)

05:50.884 --> 05:51.719
You okay?

05:51.752 --> 05:53.721
Think she'll say yes?

05:53.754 --> 05:55.155
Not if you tell her not to.

05:55.188 --> 05:56.089
No. No.

05:56.123 --> 05:59.560
I've already treated A.B.
unfairly enough.

05:59.593 --> 06:00.761
And when I compared
our relationship

06:00.794 --> 06:02.430
to other relationships I had,

06:02.463 --> 06:03.797
relationships that were...

06:05.666 --> 06:09.169
...that probably only
existed in my head...

06:09.202 --> 06:10.871
Lavon...

06:10.904 --> 06:13.741
I'm sure they
didn't only exist in your head.

06:13.774 --> 06:15.643
You know, maybe
I'm just one of those people

06:15.676 --> 06:17.911
who doesn't get to be happy.

06:20.681 --> 06:22.816
Hey, Wade, how's
the packing going?

06:22.850 --> 06:25.553
Not bad. Mostly just throwing
stuff in garbage bags.

06:25.586 --> 06:26.954
You know me.
Mm-hmm.

06:26.987 --> 06:29.757
Can't believe I only have
two days left in BlueBell.

06:29.790 --> 06:32.660
I bet they don't have
town meetings in Atlanta.

06:32.693 --> 06:34.462
But you are gonna love it there.

06:34.495 --> 06:36.797
I've never been, but I hear
that Atlanta is great.

06:36.830 --> 06:40.167
You know, except for their
ice storms, which they have now.

06:40.200 --> 06:42.570
Hey, do you have one of those
scrapey things for the ice?

06:42.603 --> 06:43.671
An ice scraper?

06:43.704 --> 06:45.573
Yeah.
Not yet.

06:45.606 --> 06:46.774
Hmm, that's super interesting.

06:46.807 --> 06:48.809
I should go.

06:50.210 --> 06:51.512
(sighs)

06:51.545 --> 06:54.482
(clears throat)

06:54.515 --> 06:56.016
(sportscaster speaking
indistinctly over television)

06:57.718 --> 06:58.786
Another beer?

06:58.819 --> 06:59.853
Yeah.

06:59.887 --> 07:01.655
Should we order a pizza, man?

07:01.689 --> 07:03.791
Yeah.

07:03.824 --> 07:05.926
ANNOUNCER: We'll be back with
some NASCAR action after this.

07:05.959 --> 07:07.761
TODD:
Yes, it's me, Don Todd.

07:07.795 --> 07:09.196
Lavon?

07:09.229 --> 07:10.698
Are you feeling lost in life?
Lavon, Lavon, Lavon, look.

07:10.731 --> 07:13.601
Then I'm talking to you.

07:13.634 --> 07:15.603
You need this.

07:15.636 --> 07:17.605
Put down that beer.

07:17.638 --> 07:19.807
And come see me, Don Todd,

07:19.840 --> 07:21.809
reading my autobiography

07:21.842 --> 07:23.877
Don Todd on Don Todd,

07:23.911 --> 07:25.679
Tallahassee Travel Books

07:25.713 --> 07:28.582
on Apalachee Parkway
tomorrow at noon.

07:33.286 --> 07:34.688
If we leave right now,

07:34.722 --> 07:36.824
we can camp outside
the bookstore

07:36.857 --> 07:38.692
and get really great seats.

07:38.726 --> 07:39.827
Oh.

07:39.860 --> 07:41.795
Aw, but we got the weddings.

07:41.829 --> 07:42.830
They're not our weddings.

07:42.863 --> 07:44.732
Lavon, Fancie's

07:44.765 --> 07:47.000
almost burned to the ground
and I lost almost all my money.

07:47.034 --> 07:48.936
Your ex is probably
getting engaged,

07:48.969 --> 07:50.604
and you might be alone forever.

07:50.638 --> 07:52.039
Did you hear what
the man said?

07:52.072 --> 07:54.508
Put your beer down!

07:56.577 --> 07:57.578
We need this.

07:58.712 --> 07:59.747
We're gonna see Don Todd!

07:59.780 --> 08:00.981
(laughing):
We're gonna see Don Todd!
(whoops)

08:01.014 --> 08:02.249
Who's gonna see Don Todd?

08:02.282 --> 08:03.617
You are!
I'm gonna see Don Todd!

08:03.651 --> 08:04.618
Uh-huh!

08:04.652 --> 08:06.520
You gonna see Don Todd?
I am.

08:06.554 --> 08:07.521
Who's driving?
Oh, m-me!

08:07.555 --> 08:08.589
Let's go! All right.
Yeah.

08:21.569 --> 08:22.836
(hiccups)

08:34.648 --> 08:37.585
(hiccups)

08:37.618 --> 08:39.787
What are you doing?

08:39.820 --> 08:41.789
Oh, hey.

08:41.822 --> 08:42.823
Um, I-I just dropped

08:42.856 --> 08:44.291
(hiccups) my keys.

08:44.324 --> 08:45.793
And also I got you

08:45.826 --> 08:47.060
(hiccups)
a go-- a good-bye gift.

08:47.094 --> 08:48.896
Are you all right?

08:48.929 --> 08:50.598
(hiccups)
Fine.

08:50.631 --> 08:51.632
Just hiccups.

08:51.665 --> 08:52.800
It's an ice scraper.

08:52.833 --> 08:55.669
Wow.

08:55.703 --> 08:56.837
Thank you.

08:56.870 --> 08:58.338
This'll be super useful.

08:58.371 --> 08:59.707
In seven months.

08:59.740 --> 09:01.709
If another ice storm
hits Atlanta.

09:01.742 --> 09:03.310
Well, that's what I thought.
(hiccups)

09:03.343 --> 09:05.312
And I, you know,
I just want you to, um...

09:05.345 --> 09:06.914
(hiccups)
...drive safe.

09:06.947 --> 09:08.081
Because I care...

09:08.115 --> 09:10.684
about safety.

09:11.919 --> 09:13.587
Thank you.

09:13.621 --> 09:15.322
I should
(hiccups) go.

09:15.355 --> 09:17.024
Okay.
Okay.

09:19.627 --> 09:21.629
(sighs)

09:23.864 --> 09:24.932
Boo!
(shrieks)

09:26.634 --> 09:28.335
(laughs)
You're welcome.

09:28.368 --> 09:30.638
See you, Doc.

09:30.671 --> 09:31.839
See you.

09:31.872 --> 09:33.741
For two days.

09:33.774 --> 09:35.709
And then...

09:35.743 --> 09:37.778
not again.

09:37.811 --> 09:40.748
Bye.

09:40.781 --> 09:43.083
(car horn honks)

09:43.116 --> 09:45.152
(seagulls calling)

09:45.185 --> 09:47.621
(birds singing)

09:55.128 --> 09:56.930
Good morning, Blawkerites.

09:56.964 --> 09:58.966
The end of the world
is still upon us.

09:58.999 --> 10:02.736
But at least we'll see
three weddings before we go.

10:04.672 --> 10:05.706
Ow!

10:06.807 --> 10:08.141
I'm sorry.

10:09.142 --> 10:11.645
Probably.

10:13.080 --> 10:15.082
(cell phone ringing)

10:20.721 --> 10:23.691
(groans)

10:23.724 --> 10:24.892
Yallo?

10:24.925 --> 10:26.393
Where are you?
Oh, uh...

10:26.426 --> 10:27.427
Tallahassee.

10:27.460 --> 10:29.963
We're gonna meet Don Todd
live and in person.

10:29.997 --> 10:31.398
(laughs)
Amazing!

10:31.431 --> 10:32.265
ZOE:
Well, turn around

10:32.299 --> 10:34.434
and come home. I need you.
(hiccups)

10:34.467 --> 10:36.837
I went to see Wade last night,
and it hit me.

10:36.870 --> 10:38.105
He's leaving and...

10:38.138 --> 10:39.673
Oh, Big Z...

10:39.707 --> 10:41.141
I don't know, maybe...

10:41.174 --> 10:42.776
Look, Zoe, just
express how you feel.

10:42.810 --> 10:44.144
Don't-don't
keep it inside.

10:44.177 --> 10:46.079
Live fearlessly.

10:46.113 --> 10:48.215
Live like...
Don Todd!

10:48.248 --> 10:50.117
Don Todd.
Don Todd.

10:50.150 --> 10:51.418
Oh, but I have
to go. Bye.

10:51.451 --> 10:53.220
Hello? Lavon? Hello?

10:54.955 --> 10:57.157
Oh, Mr. Todd,
it is a tremendous honor.

10:57.190 --> 10:58.726
A pleasure!

10:58.759 --> 11:00.160
Two people?

11:00.193 --> 11:01.962
Two people showed up
for a book reading.

11:03.063 --> 11:04.164
Well, I'm sure that
everybody just,

11:04.197 --> 11:05.465
you know, went to
the wrong place.

11:05.498 --> 11:07.667
Or there was...
there was weather.

11:08.969 --> 11:10.170
Two people!

11:10.203 --> 11:11.739
That's twice as many
as last time.

11:11.772 --> 11:13.040
Amazing.

11:13.073 --> 11:14.908
Well, what are we waiting for?

11:14.942 --> 11:15.943
Let's go!

11:17.878 --> 11:19.880
(laughing)

11:23.083 --> 11:24.852
Good morning, beautiful.

11:24.885 --> 11:25.919
Mmm...

11:25.953 --> 11:27.454
Hi, there.

11:27.487 --> 11:30.457
So, I-I know you're still
considering my proposal.

11:30.490 --> 11:32.459
Mm-hmm.
I am hoping with every
fiber of my being

11:32.492 --> 11:33.861
you say yes.

11:33.894 --> 11:34.928
And I don't want
to rush you.

11:34.962 --> 11:37.197
But, also, I want us to go
into this whole thing

11:37.230 --> 11:38.932
with eyes open.

11:38.966 --> 11:40.934
No... secrets.

11:40.968 --> 11:42.502
Oh, I agree.

11:42.535 --> 11:45.305
But...
I don't have any secrets.

11:46.874 --> 11:48.075
I have something to show you.

11:48.108 --> 11:49.943
Is it your closet?

11:49.977 --> 11:51.178
The one you never let me in?

11:51.211 --> 11:52.980
Oh, I'm
really

11:53.013 --> 11:54.982
excited.
Is it really messy?

11:55.015 --> 11:56.750
Is there a picture of you,

11:56.784 --> 11:58.485
but you're old
and hideous?

11:58.518 --> 12:00.754
Is it your grandma's skeleton,
and she is dressed

12:00.788 --> 12:02.189
like Roma Downey
from Touched by an Angel?

12:02.222 --> 12:03.991
No. No dead pets.
No skeletons.

12:04.024 --> 12:05.993
But, um,
well...

12:06.026 --> 12:08.261
a... a-a quirk.

12:11.198 --> 12:13.100
That's a lot of sneakers.

12:13.133 --> 12:14.501
A lot of
the exact same sneakers.

12:14.534 --> 12:15.535
Mmm...

12:15.568 --> 12:17.170
They're my favorites.

12:17.204 --> 12:19.106
They're just the right
width and fit.

12:19.139 --> 12:21.008
Perfect
arch support.

12:23.043 --> 12:23.977
I know it's weird.

12:24.011 --> 12:26.914
I hope it's not so weird
that you'll say no.

12:26.947 --> 12:27.981
It's a little weird.

12:28.015 --> 12:29.883
Yeah.
But it-it,

12:29.917 --> 12:32.519
it doesn't change
how I feel about you.

12:32.552 --> 12:34.121
But I
still need

12:34.154 --> 12:35.989
a little more time, okay?

12:36.023 --> 12:37.190
No problem.

12:37.224 --> 12:38.525
Just gonna go for a run.

12:38.558 --> 12:41.261
Then I'm gonna wear these
to breakfast, yeah.

12:41.294 --> 12:43.864
(hiccups)

12:43.897 --> 12:46.033
Our goal is to open up
four more Rammer Jammers

12:46.066 --> 12:47.835
in the South
in the next two years.

12:47.868 --> 12:50.037
In ten, maybe you'll be
the next Bubba Gump.

12:50.070 --> 12:52.039
I do love
popcorn shrimp.

12:52.072 --> 12:53.140
(laughs)

12:53.173 --> 12:54.574
Love him!

12:54.607 --> 12:57.010
What local color.
So...

12:57.044 --> 12:58.879
so I'll be running the Rammer
Jammer in Atlanta, right?

12:58.912 --> 13:00.914
You'll work at corporate
with us.

13:00.948 --> 13:02.249
Oversee things.

13:02.282 --> 13:04.051
