to drive across the state
to tell me.

26:05.665 --> 26:09.802
So today I'm telling you...

26:09.836 --> 26:11.671
I love you.

26:11.704 --> 26:13.172
(audience gasps)

26:14.974 --> 26:17.343
So, um...

26:17.376 --> 26:18.778
I told you.

26:20.713 --> 26:22.581
(clears throat)

26:45.004 --> 26:46.773
Nice outfit.

26:46.806 --> 26:49.375
Crickett needed an extra
bridesmaid, so...

26:49.408 --> 26:50.977
So you...

26:51.010 --> 26:53.946
decided to dress
like a, a human cupcake.

26:53.980 --> 26:55.181
That's adorable.

26:57.016 --> 27:00.687
Look, uh,
I got to finish packing.

27:00.720 --> 27:03.122
The investors are coming over
for a final meeting,

27:03.155 --> 27:05.124
and then I take off.

27:05.157 --> 27:06.993
Wait. What?!

27:07.026 --> 27:08.828
That's all you're gonna say?

27:10.863 --> 27:12.799
What do you want me to say?

27:12.832 --> 27:14.867
Oh, I don't know.
I mean, you could acknowledge

27:14.901 --> 27:16.102
how I said I loved you.

27:16.135 --> 27:17.870
And then how
you just walked away?

27:17.904 --> 27:19.739
I guess...

27:19.772 --> 27:23.810
I guess
I didn't know what to say.

27:23.843 --> 27:25.144
Or I did.

27:25.177 --> 27:27.714
Just I didn't want
to say it there...

27:27.747 --> 27:29.081
at the Rammer Jammer.

27:30.917 --> 27:33.019
Zoe, you and I,

27:33.052 --> 27:34.186
we-we tried to make this work.

27:34.220 --> 27:35.855
We tried for a long time.

27:35.888 --> 27:37.189
And it just...

27:37.223 --> 27:38.891
it just didn't.

27:38.925 --> 27:41.227
And no small part of that
is my fault.

27:41.260 --> 27:45.131
I agree. And no small part
of that was mine.

27:45.164 --> 27:46.899
We weren't ready then,
but we are now.

27:46.933 --> 27:48.901
We deserve another chance.

27:48.935 --> 27:52.171
Maybe I thought that once,
but...

27:53.973 --> 27:55.041
I got to go.

27:55.074 --> 27:57.043
And you got
your wedding to get to.

28:05.885 --> 28:09.055
You were right. Visiting
BlueBell has been so inspiring.

28:09.088 --> 28:11.023
So, you'll go back
to doing your show?

28:11.057 --> 28:12.725
Forget about throwing
in the towel?

28:12.759 --> 28:14.693
Throw in the towel? Never!
You can't!

28:17.229 --> 28:20.199
My retirement depends on how
well I do on my next hole.

28:20.232 --> 28:21.934
Gentlemen...

28:24.036 --> 28:25.471
wish me luck.

28:25.504 --> 28:29.776
I'm about to take the
most dangerous shot of my life.

28:29.809 --> 28:32.278
More dangerous
than when you putted

28:32.311 --> 28:34.080
into the mouth of the python?

28:34.113 --> 28:36.115
More dangerous than when
you made eagle

28:36.148 --> 28:37.950
from the actual nest
of an eagle?

28:37.984 --> 28:39.285
You boys want to come with me?

28:39.318 --> 28:40.753
Are you kidding?
Obviously!

28:40.787 --> 28:41.320
Shotgun!

28:44.957 --> 28:49.161
I have been making these sounds
for (hiccups) hours!

28:49.195 --> 28:51.497
I looked it up
on the Internet,

28:51.530 --> 28:54.801
and could have pneumonia,
pleurisy or (hiccups)
pharyngitis.

28:54.834 --> 28:55.902
We're (hiccups) dying.

28:55.935 --> 28:57.804
(hiccups)
On my wedding day!

28:57.837 --> 28:59.839
ZOE:
You know, I had
hiccups yesterday,

28:59.872 --> 29:01.908
and I think mine were caused
because I had something

29:01.941 --> 29:02.775
I needed to say.

29:02.809 --> 29:04.844
And then when I said it,
they went away.

29:04.877 --> 29:06.813
I don't (hiccups)
know what you're
talking about.

29:06.846 --> 29:09.148
I don't have (hiccups)
anything to say.

29:09.181 --> 29:10.282
Me (hiccups) either!

29:10.316 --> 29:12.018
Sadie!

29:12.051 --> 29:14.220
You're pulling me
too (hiccups) tight.

29:14.253 --> 29:15.254
Stop!

29:15.287 --> 29:17.890
Sorry, Crickett.

29:17.924 --> 29:19.191
Crickett,
what's going on?

29:19.225 --> 29:22.061
Nothing! (hiccups)

29:22.094 --> 29:27.033
Honey, we've all admired
what you've done

29:27.066 --> 29:29.268
to keep your (hiccups)
marriage together.

29:29.301 --> 29:32.271
But if there is some
insurmountable obstacle

29:32.304 --> 29:35.274
in your relationship,
everyone will understand

29:35.307 --> 29:38.110
if you don't want
to keep up the charade.

29:40.146 --> 29:41.914
(hiccups)

29:44.316 --> 29:48.054
WADE: Wow, they, uh, they all
look exactly the same.

29:48.087 --> 29:50.356
People need to know
from the second they enter,

29:50.389 --> 29:51.891
they're in a Rammer Jammer.

29:51.924 --> 29:52.959
Right.

29:52.992 --> 29:54.293
Authentic
Alabama cuisine.

29:54.326 --> 29:56.028
In North Carolina?

29:56.062 --> 29:57.864
Yeah. Who are you?

29:57.897 --> 30:01.133
Joel. Um, Innocent,
enthusiastic bystander.

30:01.167 --> 30:02.268
And soon to be silent one.

30:02.301 --> 30:04.170
Hey, I got you a present.

30:04.203 --> 30:06.238
All right, I love presents.
(chuckles)

30:06.272 --> 30:07.239
Oh...

30:07.273 --> 30:08.274
It's called a tie.

30:08.307 --> 30:10.009
You're gonna
need it in Atlanta.

30:10.042 --> 30:11.243
I'll let you say
your good-byes.

30:11.277 --> 30:13.379
All right.
Joel.

30:16.615 --> 30:18.985
What, you think it's a bad idea?

30:19.018 --> 30:21.187
I just don't really see you
as a tie guy.

30:21.220 --> 30:24.290
You like making up drinks
and adjusting the menu,

30:24.323 --> 30:26.158
breaking up bar fights.
That's you.

30:26.192 --> 30:28.160
Yeah, well,
maybe a super rich guy

30:28.194 --> 30:31.630
with, like, four porn star
girlfriends is also me.

30:31.663 --> 30:33.032
You never know until you try.

30:36.435 --> 30:40.106
*

30:41.673 --> 30:43.275
GEORGE:
So, I don't understand it.

30:43.309 --> 30:45.377
Where-Where are you gonna hit
your shot from?

30:45.411 --> 30:47.146
There's not even a dangerous
intersection around.

30:47.179 --> 30:48.214
Or alligator swamp.

30:48.247 --> 30:49.348
Or golf course.

30:49.381 --> 30:51.884
Boys, today
we're gonna take a mulligan

30:51.918 --> 30:53.619
on the great Fairway of Life.

30:53.652 --> 30:55.121
What does that
mean exactly?

30:55.154 --> 30:58.357
Well, yesterday...

30:58.390 --> 31:01.961
after hearing
that little doctor talk,

31:01.994 --> 31:05.231
I realized I spent all these
years trying to make

31:05.264 --> 31:06.665
these impossible holes

31:06.698 --> 31:09.401
because I have an enormous one
in my heart.

31:09.435 --> 31:12.338
Wait-- we are going to see you
play golf, right?

31:12.371 --> 31:16.275
No. We're going to Pensacola

31:16.308 --> 31:19.045
to tell my ex-wife
that I want her back.

31:22.014 --> 31:23.315
Uh, that doesn't
sound like fun.

31:23.349 --> 31:25.985
Not at all.
Shotgun.

31:29.288 --> 31:30.256
What's the delay?

31:30.289 --> 31:32.024
I don't know.

31:32.058 --> 31:34.060
I'm not really a bridesmaid,
just a stand-in.

31:34.093 --> 31:35.394
Ah, we'll start soon.

31:35.427 --> 31:36.963
You know Stanley.

31:36.996 --> 31:38.664
He's such a perfectionist.

31:38.697 --> 31:39.966
That's one thing he is.

31:39.999 --> 31:42.068
(chuckles)

31:42.101 --> 31:45.004
Oh, Lemon.
Another glass of champagne.

31:45.037 --> 31:46.472
You look like something
Hello Kitty coughed up.

31:46.505 --> 31:48.107
Thank you.
Although I really don't need

31:48.140 --> 31:49.976
to be insulted anymore today.

31:50.009 --> 31:51.910
Zoe.

31:53.345 --> 31:55.181
Listen, um.

31:55.214 --> 31:58.184
I heard about your little
outburst at Meatball's wedding.

31:58.217 --> 31:59.285
Ooh!

31:59.318 --> 32:01.053
Must've been humiliating.
(laughs)

32:01.087 --> 32:03.089
But also sort of brave.

32:03.122 --> 32:05.291
I'm impressed.

32:05.324 --> 32:06.692
What did Wade say?

32:06.725 --> 32:07.960
Not much.

32:07.994 --> 32:11.263
I'm sorry.

32:11.297 --> 32:13.232
You know, Zoe, maybe it's time

32:13.265 --> 32:15.968
for both of us to realize that
there are no second chances.

32:16.002 --> 32:18.704
I was once in a great

32:18.737 --> 32:20.006
relationship.

32:20.039 --> 32:21.407
Two, actually.

32:21.440 --> 32:24.176
But then I just
realized that

32:24.210 --> 32:25.978
holding onto the
memories of those

32:26.012 --> 32:27.713
have just been keeping me
from finding happiness.

32:27.746 --> 32:30.116
So, tonight

32:30.149 --> 32:33.219
I will be boarding
the S.S. Desperation.

32:33.252 --> 32:35.321
You're going on a cruise?

32:35.354 --> 32:38.324
Yes, I'm gonna find
a new beginning.

32:38.357 --> 32:40.726
Or an iceberg.

32:40.759 --> 32:42.028
Whatever comes first.

32:42.061 --> 32:43.996
(piano starts playing)

32:44.030 --> 32:45.464
Got to go!

33:10.489 --> 33:12.391
(Crickett hiccupping)

33:15.094 --> 33:17.096
Are you all right?

33:23.569 --> 33:24.770
Stop the music!

33:24.803 --> 33:27.073
Please.

33:27.106 --> 33:28.474
What? Why are we stopping?

33:28.507 --> 33:31.077
I'm sorry, Stanley.

33:31.110 --> 33:33.512
Folks, I'm
(hiccups) sorry.

33:33.545 --> 33:36.448
I can't do this.

33:36.482 --> 33:38.217
It's 2014.
(hiccups)

33:38.250 --> 33:41.120
Nobody has to pretend
to be something

33:41.153 --> 33:42.554
they're not anymore.
(hiccups)

33:43.855 --> 33:45.291
It's time you knew the truth.

33:45.324 --> 33:48.294
I am gay!

33:48.327 --> 33:51.097
(crowd gasps)

33:51.130 --> 33:53.132
What?

34:01.440 --> 34:02.841
Look at that.

34:02.874 --> 34:05.344
My hiccups are gone.

34:19.358 --> 34:21.827
Give Sylvie and Brando my best.

34:21.860 --> 34:23.529
You know, you don't have to go.

34:23.562 --> 34:24.830
Already told everyone
I was leaving.

34:24.862 --> 34:25.964
And they'd be happy
to have you back.

34:25.996 --> 34:29.268
Just step back behind the bar
and into your old life.

34:29.301 --> 34:31.337
Nah. No.

34:31.370 --> 34:32.338
So, what then?

34:40.212 --> 34:42.848
Oh, I see.

34:42.880 --> 34:44.183
Yup.

34:48.620 --> 34:51.257
Don Todd in love.

34:51.290 --> 34:53.259
He's not supposed to care about
love-- that's why he's my hero.

34:53.292 --> 34:55.161
More manly.

34:55.194 --> 34:57.163
No, it's embarrassing
is what it is.

34:57.196 --> 34:59.165
I just got off the phone
with Wanda.

34:59.198 --> 35:00.466
We have really missed a lot.

35:00.499 --> 35:03.469
Davis Polk has
200 pairs of sneakers.

35:03.502 --> 35:05.871
Lemon's going on a Belles and
Bachelors Cruise for a month,

35:05.904 --> 35:08.207
claims she's coming
back engaged.

35:08.240 --> 35:11.177
And Crickett is gay.
Wait, what?

35:11.210 --> 35:12.344
DAVIS:
 Man, that's surprising.

35:12.378 --> 35:14.180
(chuckles)
Crickett?

35:14.213 --> 35:15.481
I didn't see that one coming.

35:15.514 --> 35:17.883
(hiccups)

35:17.916 --> 35:19.185
A.B., are you okay?

35:19.218 --> 35:20.486
Yeah.
(hiccups)

35:20.519 --> 35:21.687
Are you sure?

35:21.720 --> 35:24.656
Um, just...
(quiet laugh)

35:24.690 --> 35:26.492
I have my answer.

35:26.525 --> 35:28.394
Y-You do?

35:28.427 --> 35:29.428
I-Is it...?

35:29.461 --> 35:30.596
TODD:
 Great news!

35:30.629 --> 35:32.598
It went well?
Well...

35:32.631 --> 35:34.900
did you ever see
that episode where I got stung

35:34.933 --> 35:36.468
by the brood of jellyfish?

35:36.502 --> 35:38.370
Then I lost my nine iron
to the octopus?

35:38.404 --> 35:39.371
Yeah.

35:39.405 --> 35:41.440
This was way worse than that.

35:41.473 --> 35:43.409
Miss Glendora

35:43.442 --> 35:44.610
has moved on.

35:44.643 --> 35:46.512
I have missed my chance.

35:46.545 --> 35:49.181
Then, why are you so happy?

35:49.215 --> 35:49.981
Well, because now I can move on.

35:50.015 --> 35:51.550
See, I laid it all out
on the table.

35:51.583 --> 35:54.220
Now I know I've done
everything I could.

35:54.253 --> 35:55.387
Everything you could.

35:55.421 --> 35:56.222
In hindsight,

35:56.255 --> 35:58.490
I should've done it
four years ago.

35:58.524 --> 36:00.626
Now I don't have to spend
every day thinking

36:00.659 --> 36:02.561
maybe she feels it, too.

36:02.594 --> 36:05.231
And it's like
the sun has come out

36:05.264 --> 36:07.533
on a brand-new day for Don Todd.

36:07.566 --> 36:10.236
Like any other man
in my shoes,

36:10.269 --> 36:11.537
I want to go hit a few holes.

36:11.570 --> 36:13.239
Who's with me?

36:13.272 --> 36:14.240
This guy.

36:14.273 --> 36:15.241
Actually, I have to go.

36:15.274 --> 36:17.243
Uh, was that a rent-a-car place
on the corner?

36:17.276 --> 36:18.377
What? Yeah.

36:18.410 --> 36:19.411
(stammers)

36:19.445 --> 36:21.947
ANNABETH:
 I admire

36:21.980 --> 36:24.383
how organized
you keep your closet.

36:24.416 --> 36:26.218
All those (hiccups) sneakers

36:26.252 --> 36:28.254
make you more lovable to me.

36:28.287 --> 36:29.288
It lets me (hiccups)

36:29.321 --> 36:31.457
see that you have flaws.

36:31.490 --> 36:33.592
That you're not just
that perfect knight.

36:33.625 --> 36:34.660
AnnaBeth, you've been
complimenting me

36:34.693 --> 36:36.295
for the last five minutes.

36:36.328 --> 36:38.297
Is this going
where I think it is?

36:38.330 --> 36:40.799
Or is there a big "but" coming?

36:42.000 --> 36:42.968
But...

36:43.001 --> 36:46.705
I've been in
your position.

36:46.738 --> 36:49.275
I-I've been the rebound person.

36:49.308 --> 36:52.711
Which is why I know
you deserve more

36:52.744 --> 36:55.514
than to settle for someone

36:55.547 --> 36:57.416
who's still in love
with someone else.

37:00.619 --> 37:01.987
Don?

37:02.020 --> 37:03.322
Might I ask exactly
what happened

37:03.355 --> 37:05.524
between you and your wife?

37:05.557 --> 37:07.793
We drove each other crazy
whenever we were together.

37:07.826 --> 37:09.695
It's like we fought
because we were

37:09.728 --> 37:10.996
afraid to let the other know

37:11.029 --> 37:13.399
how deeply we felt.

37:13.432 --> 37:14.333
That's beautiful.

37:14.366 --> 37:17.002
I think there's
a driving range around here.

37:17.035 --> 37:18.404
You all in?

37:18.437 --> 37:20.472
Um, actually...

37:20.506 --> 37:22.474
I'm gonna need you to
drop me off somewhere.

37:22.508 --> 37:26.244
'Cause I have to get to the
woman that drives me crazy.

37:32.784 --> 37:34.420
SYLVIE:
 My first husband Jerry

37:34.453 --> 37:38.324
was the love of my life,
and when he died,

37:38.357 --> 37:40.326
I felt like...
The days were just things

37:40.359 --> 37:42.561
to pass the time
till you joined Jerry.

37:42.594 --> 37:44.463
And I joined
my Margaret May.

37:44.496 --> 37:45.764
And then...
I met you.

37:45.797 --> 37:48.033
SYLVIE:
My miracle.

37:48.066 --> 37:49.635
Not only do I feel love again.

37:49.668 --> 37:51.303
I feel joy.

37:51.337 --> 37:52.304
Joy.

37:52.338 --> 37:53.439
And I want to thank you

37:53.472 --> 37:56.675
for what I never thought
was possible.

37:56.708 --> 37:58.544
True love twice.

37:58.577 --> 37:59.745
A second chance.

38:03.382 --> 38:04.683
(crowd clapping)

38:07.686 --> 38:10.055
Ooh.
(chuckles)

38:10.088 --> 38:10.756
(glass shatters)

38:10.789 --> 38:12.324
Yes! Mazel tov!

38:17.663 --> 38:19.331
(line ringing)

38:19.365 --> 38:20.699
Why are you calling me?

38:20.732 --> 38:22.668
Because second chances exist.

38:22.701 --> 38:24.570
We can find love again.
Don't get on that boat.

38:24.603 --> 38:26.071
I can't hear you. What?

38:26.104 --> 38:27.406
Don't give up on true love!

38:27.439 --> 38:28.574
I'm sorry, I don't get...

38:28.607 --> 38:30.075
Hello?

38:30.108 --> 38:31.477
Lemon? You heard me?

38:31.510 --> 38:32.678
You're coming back, right?

38:32.711 --> 38:35.547
Hello?

38:35.581 --> 38:37.449
MAN:
Haven't you heard?

38:37.483 --> 38:39.585
Cell service is
terrible on the ship.

38:39.618 --> 38:42.087
You won't be able to make
any calls for 30 days.

38:42.120 --> 38:45.591
I guess we'll just need to find
other ways to pass the time.

38:45.624 --> 38:47.359
(laughs)

38:56.134 --> 38:59.505
*

39:13.785 --> 39:15.487
(clears throat)

39:17.689 --> 39:19.391
What are you doing here?

39:19.425 --> 39:20.859
I thought you'd be
on the road to Atlanta.

39:20.892 --> 39:22.761
I turned it down.

39:22.794 --> 39:25.531
Yeah, I think one Rammer Jammer
is enough for this world.

39:25.564 --> 39:26.465
Really?

39:26.498 --> 39:27.466
They wanted me to wear

39:27.499 --> 39:28.700
a suit and tie, you know?

39:28.734 --> 39:30.636
Work a desk job.
It's not for me.

39:31.903 --> 39:33.872
Don't read too much
into it, all right?

39:33.905 --> 39:34.740
Okay.

39:34.773 --> 39:36.442
Seriously.

39:36.475 --> 39:37.476
Okay.

39:37.509 --> 39:39.511
(humming along with music)

39:52.924 --> 39:54.626
Thank you guys so much!

39:54.660 --> 39:56.662
Hurry up!
The boat's leaving in a minute!

39:56.695 --> 39:57.663
G. Tuck,

39:57.696 --> 39:58.897
go tell Lemon how you feel!

39:58.930 --> 40:01.900
Viva romance!

40:01.933 --> 40:04.402
Yeah.

40:05.937 --> 40:07.673
Excuse me, sorry.

40:07.706 --> 40:09.608
No, no, no, no! Hold on!

40:09.641 --> 40:11.777
You have to let me on that boat.

40:11.810 --> 40:12.978
Sorry, sir, the ship
is already underway.

40:13.011 --> 40:15.447
No, no!
We're all clear for departure.

40:16.815 --> 40:18.950
Lemon!

40:19.818 --> 40:21.186
Lemon!

40:21.219 --> 40:22.654
Lemon!

40:22.688 --> 40:23.789
(whistling)

40:23.822 --> 40:25.657
Lemon Breeland.

40:25.691 --> 40:26.925
Yes, I've heard of you.

40:26.958 --> 40:29.194
Oh, well, don't believe
everything you hear.

40:29.227 --> 40:30.596
(both laugh)

40:30.629 --> 40:31.830
(hiccups)

40:31.863 --> 40:33.699
MAN:
Find a good one.
WOMAN:
Call me when you get there.

40:33.732 --> 40:35.934
Lemon!

40:37.736 --> 40:39.571
(ship horn blows)

40:39.605 --> 40:41.039
Lemon!

40:43.709 --> 40:44.743
George?

40:45.844 --> 40:47.713
Lavon?

40:53.852 --> 40:55.687
No.

40:55.721 --> 40:58.023
No, no, no...

40:58.056 --> 41:01.627
BOTH:
No, no, no, no, no, no, no!

41:02.994 --> 41:05.931
200 pairs of shoes, huh?

41:05.964 --> 41:08.734
Yeah, I think you made
the right move there.

41:10.569 --> 41:12.971
Oh, ma-may I cut in?

41:13.004 --> 41:15.006
By all means.

41:19.277 --> 41:21.046
Hey there.

41:21.079 --> 41:23.782
Stop looking at me like that.

